ss call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:187:### Pipeline: Fix javac test failures + PR creation\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:262:- JaCoCo XML coverage parser:\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:386:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:387:failure output in normal prompt templates.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:421:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:452:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:456:| `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4` | `pi` | `javac_iterative` |\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:459:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:482:see `docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md`.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:502:- Parse JaCoCo XML coverage:\nforge/ai_workflows/core/basic_iterative_strategy.py:209:                    \"agent: test failed before nativeTest; sending failure output back to agent\",\nforge/utility_scripts/fixture_github.py:303:            self._prepare_version_failure_worktree(issue, label, worktree_path)\nforge/utility_scripts/fixture_github.py:377:    def _prepare_version_failure_worktree(\nforge/utility_scripts/fixture_github.py:383:        \"\"\"Mask the requested version so a failure fixture replays a current -> new upgrade.\nforge/utility_scripts/fixture_github.py:386:        all three model a scheduled-compatibility failure where the requested version is\nforge/fixture_github_issues/fails-native-ima