s/functional-spec.md:73:### FS-forge-code-coverage-improvement: Code coverage improvement\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:76:code coverage, not only dynamic-access coverage (see\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:77:§WF-code-coverage-improvement), broadening the library coverage outcome\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:78:described in §GOAL-maximize-library-coverage. The workflow creates or improves\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:82:Those tests must live in a separate code coverage test suite, not in the test\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:86:dynamic-access coverage workflow defined in §WF-improve-library-coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:88:coverage asks whether tests exercise calls that require reachability metadata;\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:89:code coverage improvement asks whether tests exercise the broader library API\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:92:metadata-relevant coverage from broader behavior coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:109:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:110:| **Dynamic-access exhaust report** | Durable coordinate-scoped JSON state for chunked dynamic-access work. It records the coordinate, issue number, class threshold, processed/exhausted/failed classes, and the latest published chunk PR/commit. It is stored in a stable location derived from the target test suite (for example under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`) so orchestration scripts can find it from the coordinate alone. It does not predefine all chunks; each resume regenerates the current dynamic-access report and filters out exhausted classes. Specified by §WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:111:| **Chunked dynamic-access workflow** | Dynamic-access generation mode for oversized `library-new-request` and `library-update-request` issues. `forge_metadata.py` owns the class threshold decision and passes the current chunk size to the workflow. The workflow processes at most that many uncovered classes, publishes that chunk, then resumes after the chunk PR merges. PR linking rules are in §WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:113:| **Library update target** | The metadata and test directories selected for a `library-update-request` coordinate (§WF-improve-library-coverage.3). Resolution records the requested coordinate, match type (`tested-version`, `metadata-version`, `default-for`, or `new-version`), matched index entry, resolved metadata version, resolved test version, and edit directories. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:142:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:143:  workflows (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:156:  Gradle or Native Image failure that triggered them. This is a hard\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:170:  If the current dynamic-access report has more uncovered classes than this\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:178:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:191:  hard setup failure.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:206:  `improve-coverage-…`, `fix-javac-…`, `fix-java-run-…`,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:215:coverage, and status evidence stays attached to the library version it describes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:216:(§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage). During a run, in-flight metrics are staged\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:255:command that would require `sudo` is a local verification failure, not an\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:312:the failure is caused by the repository itself. After the gate passes, Forge\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:322:failure label. Forge must apply it only when the available evidence shows that\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:326:Valid human-intervention cases are semantic or generation failures inside\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:335:- Dynamic-access coverage remains missing or suspiciously low after a\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:340:- Publication detects a severe metadata, test, or coverage anomaly that makes\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:343:Forge must not use `human-intervention` for failures that are only external or\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:345:download failures, GitHub API/status failures, rate limits, runner outages,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:346:temporary registry unavailability, and similar environmental failures must be\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:347:reported as infrastructure failures, retried or preserved with diagnostics as\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:392:noise, GitHub status/API failures, Maven download failures, or other external\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:429:failures while preparing the validation candidate, such as fetch failures,\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:431:failures.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:441:| `RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY` | A chunked dynamic-access run reached a reviewable class boundary and §FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification passed for the current part. The current part is PR-eligible, and the issue must not be resumed until the part PR has merged. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:444:The exit code is `0` for PR-eligible statuses and `1` for failure.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:449:must run or refresh the dynamic-access report before choosing the execution\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:450:mode. If the current report has more uncovered dynamic-access classes than the\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:459:`chunked-dynamic-access` label. The normal project status remains the run-state\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:465:by §WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:471:(§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:483:|