ge (§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage), shorten the path from opened\n./forge/docs/goals.md:9:(§GOAL-minimize-generation-cost), and turn recurring failures into better\n./forge/docs/goals.md:12:# GOAL-maximize-library-coverage: Maximize library coverage\n./forge/docs/goals.md:14:Forge should make supported JVM library coverage as high as practical. It should\n./forge/docs/goals.md:15:add metadata and tests for unsupported libraries, improve coverage for\n./forge/docs/goals.md:31:coverage, and reviewability. It should use the least tokens and compute needed\n./stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-compatible/3.2.19/execution-metrics.json:15:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-compatible/3.2.19/execution-metrics.json:29:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 100.0\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:17: * Generates a per-class dynamic-access coverage report for matching coordinates.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:20: * {@code metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json}\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:72:            getLogger().quiet(\"Wrote dynamic-access coverage report for {} to {}.\", coordinate, outputFile);\n./stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-wordspec_3/3.2.19/execution-metrics.json:15:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.scalatest/scalatest-wordspec_3/3.2.19/execution-metrics.json:49:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 35.12\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDependencyGraphTask.java:266:                        // Non-retryable failure for this URL; try next if available\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:43: * Resolves an arbitrary Maven coordinate and computes dynamic-access totals without repo-tracked tests.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:67:                        \"reports/external-dynamic-access/summary.json\"\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:79:                .dir(\"tmp/external-dynamic-access/\" + sanitize(coordinates.toString()))\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:136:                imageDir.resolve(\"dynamic-access\")\n./forge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:16:`library-update-request` route to dynamic-access generation\n./forge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:17:(§WF-dynamic-access-workflow) and coverage improvement\n./forge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:18:(§WF-improve-library-coverage); `fails-javac-compile` and `fails-java-run` route\n./forge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:74:Successful or chunk-ready runs (§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking) proceed to\n./forge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:112:afterward; a review timeout or non-zero Codex exit is a review failure, not an\n./docs/functional-spec.md:4:§GOAL-tested-metadata §GOAL-broad-version-coverage §GOAL-fresh-metadata §GOAL-protect-shipped-metadata\n./docs/functional-spec.md:23:| **Repository automation (Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/functional-spec.md](../forge/docs/functional-spec.md). |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:47:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` mirror of per-version metrics — `stats.json` (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information) produced by the harness, alongside the schema-validated `execution-metrics.json` each Forge run records.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:59:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:68:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:78:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/functional-spec.md:79:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/functional-spec.md:80:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n./docs/functional-spec.md:82:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/functional-spec.md:88:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n./docs/functional-spec.md:90:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:96:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:97:2. **Fix `javac` failures** raised by a library version bump.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:98:3. **Fix native-image runtime failures** raised by a library version bump.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:99:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:110:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:126:| `chunked-dynamic-access` | Issue | Forge split dynamic-access generation for this issue into class-aligned chunks because the uncovered class count exceeded the configured threshold. Normal project status controls whether Forge may claim the next chunk. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:220:- **Index coverage.** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Coverage non-regression.** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/functional-spec.md:242:- **Full sweep.** `test-all-metadata` runs only on schedule or manual dispatch in the main repository, uses 85 batches, creates one aggregated GitHub issue per failed `(library, version)` pair across configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations and native-image modes, and is release-blocking when failures are found.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:262:- **Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:282:- GitHub issues for new-version compatibility failures, one per `(library, version)`.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:354:§GOAL-broad-version-coverage §GOAL-fresh-metadata\n./docs/functional-spec.md:356:The repository must keep its tested-version coverage current as upstream\n./docs/functional-spec.md:364:files one tracking issue per version that fails. The failure issues are the\n./docs/functional-spec.md:393:per version. On failure it bisects the failing stage in order —\n./docs/functional-spec.md:396:classify the failure, records the first failing version, and stops walking that\n./docs/functional-spec.md:399:failure with its stage, failing version, reproducer command, runner-log URL, and\n./docs/functional-spec.md:419:#### 4. Opening failure tickets\n./docs/functional-spec.md:422:GitHub issue. The title is `[Automation] <primary failure stage> fails for\n./docs/functional-spec.md:433:`origin/master` already supports is treated as a stale failure and skipped.\n./docs/tck.md:106:| `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`, `generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix` | Discover newer upstream versions and build the compatibility matrix (§GOAL-broad-version-coverage). |\n./docs/tck.md:108:## 8. Reporting, stats, coverage, and packaging\n./docs/tck.md:112:| `jacocoTestReport` | JaCoCo coverage for a coordinate. |\n./docs/tck.md:113:| `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`